# Design Styles Reference

Detailed style definitions, palette recommendations, and font pairings for use with the `ui-ux-pro-max` skill.

## UI Style Catalog (Web-Focused)

### Glassmorphism
- **Look**: Frosted glass panels, backdrop blur, transparency layers
- **Best for**: SaaS dashboards, modern landing pages, dark-mode products
- **Key CSS**: `backdrop-filter: blur(12px)`, `bg-white/10`, `border-white/20`
- **Palette**: Dark backgrounds (#0F172A, #1E293B) with white/translucent panels
- **Avoid**: Using in light mode without sufficient opacity (`bg-white/80` minimum)

### Minimalism
- **Look**: Maximum whitespace, essential elements only, precise typography
- **Best for**: Portfolios, documentation, editorial, professional services
- **Key CSS**: Large `padding`, `max-w-prose`, monochromatic palette
- **Palette**: Near-white backgrounds, slate-900 text, one accent color
- **Fonts**: Geometric sans (DM Sans, Plus Jakarta Sans) + system stack

### Brutalism
- **Look**: Raw, unpolished, bold borders, stark contrast, intentional ugliness
- **Best for**: Creative agencies, artist portfolios, tech startups
- **Key CSS**: `border-4 border-black`, solid shadows `shadow-[4px_4px_0px_black]`
- **Palette**: Black + white + one saturated accent (yellow, red, electric blue)
- **Fonts**: Clash Display, Space Mono, or bold grotesque

### Neumorphism
- **Look**: Soft extruded plastic, dual shadows, monochromatic
- **Best for**: Mobile UI, music players, device dashboards
- **Key CSS**: `shadow-[inset_2px_2px_5px_#b8b9be,-3px_-3px_7px_#fff]`
- **Palette**: Single mid-tone background with light/dark shadow variants
- **Avoid**: Small text on neumorphic surfaces (contrast issues)

### Bento Grid
- **Look**: Asymmetric card grids, feature showcases, dashboard-style layouts
- **Best for**: SaaS feature pages, portfolios, product showcases
- **Key CSS**: `grid`, varying `col-span` and `row-span`, consistent gap
- **Palette**: Light neutral backgrounds, cards with subtle borders or shadows

### Dark Mode / Cyberpunk
- **Look**: Dark backgrounds, neon accents, high contrast, glowing effects
- **Best for**: Developer tools, gaming, crypto, fintech
- **Key CSS**: `bg-gray-950`, neon text shadows, `ring-1 ring-cyan-500/20`
- **Palette**: Slate-950 base, cyan/purple/green neon accents
- **Fonts**: JetBrains Mono, Fira Code, or geometric sans

### Claymorphism
- **Look**: Inflated 3D clay shapes, pastel colors, soft shadows
- **Best for**: Children's apps, creative tools, playful products
- **Key CSS**: `rounded-3xl`, large soft shadows, pastel `bg-*-200`
- **Palette**: Soft pastels (rose, violet, sky, emerald in -100/-200 range)

### Flat Design
- **Look**: No shadows/gradients, bold color blocks, icon-driven
- **Best for**: Mobile apps, illustration-heavy sites, simple dashboards
- **Key CSS**: Flat `bg-*-500` colors, `rounded-lg`, no `shadow`
- **Fonts**: Rounded sans (Nunito, Quicksand)

### Editorial / Magazine
- **Look**: Mixed typography scales, pull quotes, photo-driven, asymmetric grid
- **Best for**: Blogs, news, content platforms, portfolio narratives
- **Key CSS**: Variable font sizes, `font-serif` headings, editorial spacing
- **Fonts**: Playfair Display + Source Serif (body) or Fraunces + Lora

### Skeuomorphism
- **Look**: Realistic textures, physical metaphors, detailed shadows
- **Best for**: Niche apps where familiarity matters, premium/luxury products
- **Key CSS**: Gradient-based textures, detailed `box-shadow`, subtle `border`

---

## Color Palette Recommendations by Product Type

| Product Type | Primary | Accent | Background | Text |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| SaaS / B2B | Indigo-600 | Violet-500 | Slate-50 | Slate-900 |
| E-commerce | Emerald-600 | Amber-500 | White | Gray-900 |
| Healthcare | Blue-600 | Teal-500 | Blue-50 | Slate-800 |
| Fintech | Blue-700 | Cyan-500 | Slate-900 | White |
| Beauty / Wellness | Rose-500 | Pink-400 | Rose-50 | Slate-800 |
| Creative / Agency | Violet-600 | Yellow-400 | Gray-950 | White |
| Developer Tools | Zinc-900 | Cyan-400 | Zinc-950 | Zinc-100 |
| Education | Blue-500 | Orange-400 | Blue-50 | Slate-800 |
| Gaming | Purple-700 | Fuchsia-400 | Slate-950 | White |

---

## Font Pairing Recommendations

### Professional / SaaS
- **Heading**: Inter 700 or DM Sans 700
- **Body**: Inter 400 or DM Sans 400
- **Mono**: JetBrains Mono (code blocks)

### Editorial / Content
- **Heading**: Playfair Display 700 or Fraunces 700
- **Body**: Source Serif 4 or Lora 400
- **Sans**: DM Sans (UI elements)

### Modern / Startup
- **Heading**: Clash Display 600 or Plus Jakarta Sans 700
- **Body**: Plus Jakarta Sans 400 or Outfit 400

### Minimal / Clean
- **Heading**: Geist 700 or Sora 600
- **Body**: Geist 400 or Sora 400

### Luxury / Premium
- **Heading**: Cormorant Garamond 600 or Libre Baskerville 700
- **Body**: Jost 300 or Raleway 300
- **Accent**: Cormorant Garamond italic

### Playful / Creative
- **Heading**: Nunito 800 or Quicksand 700
- **Body**: Nunito 400 or Quicksand 400
- **Accent**: Pacifico (sparingly)

### Technical / Developer
- **Heading**: Space Grotesk 600 (acceptable here — context-appropriate)
- **Body**: IBM Plex Sans 400
- **Mono**: IBM Plex Mono or JetBrains Mono

---

## Z-Index Scale

Define a consistent z-index scale to avoid stacking conflicts:

```css
/* Recommended z-index scale */
--z-base: 0;
--z-raised: 10;      /* Cards, dropdowns */
--z-dropdown: 20;    /* Popovers, tooltips */
--z-sticky: 30;      /* Sticky headers */
--z-overlay: 40;     /* Modals backdrop */
--z-modal: 50;       /* Modal dialogs */
--z-toast: 60;       /* Toast notifications */
```

---

## Chart Type Guide

| Data Type | Recommended Chart | Library |
|---|---|---|
| Trend over time | Line chart | Recharts, Chart.js |
| Category comparison | Bar chart | Recharts |
| Part-to-whole | Donut/Pie | Recharts |
| Distribution | Histogram | Recharts |
| Correlation | Scatter | Recharts |
| Hierarchy | Treemap | Recharts |
| Flow | Sankey | D3.js |
| Real-time | Area/Line with streaming | Recharts |
| Geographic | Map | Leaflet, Mapbox |
| Multi-metric | Radar | Recharts |

Always provide a table alternative for screen readers alongside charts.
</file>

